27/05/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- President Ahmet Necdet Sezer welcomed his Albanian counterpart Alfred Moisiu on Monday (26 May), describing bilateral relations as very good. 
He added that the countries share not only a common history but also a common future in EU integration. 
Sezer commended Albania's progress in efforts to become a member of NATO and pledged to provide support for preparations. 
Moisiu, in turn, said both Turkey and Albania play an important role in strengthening stability in the Balkans. 
(Hurriyet - 27/05/03; Anadolu Agency, TRT 2 - 26/05/03)
